cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.DS, cs.LG

This paper deals with image search and retrieval using a new local descriptor called Local Radon Descriptor (LRD). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of LRD for content-based medical image retrieval, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper involves the use of dense sampling and histogram generation, which are common techniques in multimedia analysis and retrieval, indicating that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to evaluate the performance of LRD, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
